On his departure, he is dismissed by the women with the usual percussion of the lips, In the same manner he enters the dwellings of the other hordesmen, always accompanied by a crowd of boys. The office of crier‚ which the noble Abipones despise, is generally performed by some juggler of advanced age and low birth. ’ Meantime they furnish the house, appointed for the meeting, with a hasty apparatus The floor is covered with the skins of tigers and of kine, upon which the guests sit. A temporary erection is made of reedS, upon which they place the hairy scalps of their slain enemies, as trophieS. When they prefer celebrating the victory without the tent in the open air, they hang these trophies upon spears fixed upright in the circle in which they sit. At sun-set, the persons invited all flock to the appointed place, where they sit down on the ground, having leathern vessels of mead set in the midst of them, though the drinking does not commence till about morning, the whole night being spent in chaunting their victorieS.
